    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "**Description of proposed changes**\r\n\r\nTo allow for spaces in arguments to PyGMT functions, this pull request modifies the `build_arg_string` function in `pygmt/helpers/utils.py` to replace space characters (` `) with the equivalent octal code (`\\040`). This enables users to do this:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nimport pygmt\r\n\r\nfig = pygmt.Figure()\r\nfig.basemap(region=[0, 2, 4, 8], projection=\"X2c\", frame=r\"WSne+tPlot Zero\")\r\nfig.show()\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that no nested double quotes (`'\"some word\"'`) are needed anymore!\r\n\r\n<!-- Please describe changes proposed and **why** you made them. If unsure, open an issue first so we can discuss.-->\r\n\r\n\r\nI have also removed some hacky workarounds that allowed for text inputs with spaces into:\r\n- `subplot`'s `autolabel`(-A) and `title` (-T) parameters - workaround added in #1125 and #822\r\n- `text`'s `-F` parameter\r\n- `psconvert`'s `prefix` (-F) parameter - workaround added in #1116\r\n\r\nAlso updated some unit tests for `fig.legend` and `fig.rose` that had used arguments like `'\"Some text\"'`.\r\n\r\n### **Special handling** of functions where spaces can't just be converted to `\\040`:\r\n- [x] Ensure that `pygmt.config(FORMAT_DATE_MAP=\"o dd\")` works (c29e63229f6c46aeb47cfe068b9f6c959728f64a) \r\n- [x] Make sure that `fig.savefig()` saves filenames with spaces properly (#1116) without `\\040` octal code characters in the filename (83c8c3b0e8c699cd52e7d539c49dabbbf7bf384c)\r\n- [x] Ensure that PROJ4 projections with spaces (e.g. `projection=\"+proj4=+longlat +ellipsoid=someplanet\"`) work, xref https://github.com/GenericMappingTools/pygmt/issues/655#issuecomment-713154812 (3ec772740823a12f906210edeed5284aa101ff12)\r\n\r\n<!-- If fixing an issue, put the issue number after the # below (no spaces). GitHub will automatically close it when this gets merged. -->\r\nFixes #247 :tada: :tada: :tada:\r\n\r\n\r\n**Reminders**\r\n\r\n- [x] Run `make format` and `make check` to make sure the code follows the style guide.\r\n- [x] Add tests for new features or tests that would have caught the bug that you're fixing.\r\n- [ ] Add new public functions/methods/classes to `doc/api/index.rst`.\r\n- [x] Write detailed docstrings for all functions/methods.\r\n- [ ] If adding new functionality, add an example to docstrings or tutorials.\r\n\r\n**Slash Commands**\r\n\r\nYou can write slash commands (`/command`) in the first line of a comment to perform\r\nspecific operations. Supported slash commands are:\r\n\r\n- `/format`: automatically format and lint the code\r\n- `/test-gmt-dev`: run full tests on the latest GMT development version\r\n",
