        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> As you can see, I have to use `\"xaf+lX label+uK\"`, not `\"xaf+l'X label'+uK\"` or `'xaf+l\"X label\"+uK'`. For me, the last two are much easier to read.\r\n\r\nI just tested all three examples and only `\"xaf+l'X label'+uK\"` doesn't work properly (it prints `'X label` instead of `X label`), but that's a known issue with using single quotes. This branch should be backwards compatible with the `'xaf+l\"X label\"+uK'` method, and it now allows for `\"xaf+lX label+uK\"` which isn't nice but works if people like that format.",
